We prompt the LLM again to assess its confidence in the generated O values.
 For each {\em SPO}, 
 top-{{2405.02732_FO0030||FO}} support passages in their enriched form (with all named entities incl. S and O) are included into the LLM prompt for in-context inference:
 ``Given this information, is {\em SPO} a correct statement?''.
 The {\em conf} classifier accepts an O candidate if the LLM gives a ``yes'' reply.
 This approach differs from the passage-based extraction of the recall-oriented stage,
 as the support passages are retrieved individually for each O-candidate.